9 An Act relating to oil and gas; amending 52 O.S.
2021, Section 318.1, as amended by Section 1, Chapter
10 24, O.S.L. 2025 (52 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 318.1),
which relates to agreement as to compliance with
11 drilling and plugging regulations; authorizing
certain operators to make voluntary election;
12 requiring certain notice; authorizing retention of
certain right; requiring certain permanence beyond
13 expiration; requiring operators to post surety by
certain date; updating statutory language; and
14 declaring an emergency.
15
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 52 O.S. 2021, Section 318.1, as
19 amended by Section 1, Chapter 24, O.S.L. 2025 (52 O.S. Supp. 2025,
20 Section 318.1), is amended to read as follows:
21 Section 318.1. A. Any person who drills or operates any well
22 for the exploration, development, or production of oil or gas, or as
23 an injection or disposal well, within this state, shall furnish in
24 writing, on forms approved by the Corporation Commission, his or her
SB1976 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 agre ement to drill, operate, and plug wells in compliance with the
2 rules of the Commission and the laws of this state, together with
3 evidence of financial ability to comply with the requirements for
4 plugging, closure of surface impoundments, removal of trash and
5 equipment as established by the rules of the Commission and by law.
6 To establish evidence of financial ability, the Commission shall
7 require:
8 1. Category A surety, which shall include a financial statement
9 listing assets and liabilities, and including a general release that
10 the information may be verified with banks and other financial
11 institutions. The statement shall prove a net worth of not less
12 than Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000.00). Category A surety will no
13 longer be accepted as valid form of surety for new operators to
14 select beginning November 1, 2025. All current operators who have
15 valid Category A surety and are in good standing with the Commission
16 will be able to retain their Category A surety for the time they are
17 a valid operator in the State of Oklahoma this state. Any operator
18 eligible to maintain Category A surety may voluntarily elect to
19 convert to Category B surety upon written notice to the Commission.
20 An operator making such election shall retain the right to revert to
21 Category A surety without penalty or additional qualification
22 requirements, provided the operator submits written notice of
23 reversion within three (3) years of the effective date of the
24 election and remains in good standing with the Commission. Upon
SB1976 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 expi ration of the three-year period, the operator shall be
2 permanently subject to Category B surety requirements; or
3 2. Category B surety, which shall include an irrevocable
4 commercial letter of credit, cash, a cashier’s check, a Certificate
5 certificate of Deposit deposit, other negotiable instrument, or a
6 blanket surety bond. Except as provided in paragraph 1 of
7 subsection B or subsection C of this section, the amount of such
8 letter of credit, cash, cashier’s check, certificate, bond, receipt,
9 or other negotiable instrument shall be based on the number of wells
10 that the person operates and shall have the option of using the
11 phase-in schedule as follows:
12 a. for one to ten wells, Twenty-five Thousand Dollars
13 ($25,000.00),
14 b. for eleven to fifty wells, operators shall post
15 Category B surety in the amount of Thirty-three
16 Thousand Three Hundred Dollars ($33,300.00) no later
17 than the due date of the operator’s Form 1006B
18 occurring during the calendar year 2026; on the due
