1 full amount of One Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars
2 ($150,000.00).
3 By the end of the year in 2028, all Category B operators shall be
4 required to post surety in the full amounts specified in paragraph 2
5 of this subsection, based upon the number of wells operated. The
6 Commission is authorized to determine a higher amount of Category B
7 surety based upon the past performance of the operator and its
8 insiders and affiliates regarding compliance with the laws of this
9 state, and any rules promulgated thereto including, but not limited
10 to, the drilling, operation, and plugging of wells, closure of
11 surface impoundments, or removal of trash and equipment, provided
12 that such higher amount shall not exceed One Hundred Fifty Thousand
13 Dollars ($150,000.00). Any instrument shall constitute an
14 unconditional promise to pay and be in a form negotiable by the
15 Commission.
16 B. 1. The Commission upon certification by any operator
17 subject to Category B surety that its plugging liability statewide
18 is less than the amount based on the number of wells operated as
19 specified in this section may allow said the operator to provide
20 Category B type surety in an amount less than the amount required by
21 this section, but at least sufficient to cover the estimated cost of
22 all plugging, closure, and removal operations currently the
23 responsibility of that operator. The liability certification
24 referred to in this subsection shall take the form of an affidavit
SB1976 HFLR Page 5
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 from a licensed well plugger estimating the costs of all plugging,
2 closure, and removal operations of the operator requesting such
3 relief. This alternative amount shall be modified upward upon the
4 assumption of additional operations by such operator, the maximum
5 amount of Category B surety to be posted not to exceed One Hundred
6 Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00).
7 2. New operators, operators who have outstanding fines or
8 contempt citations, and operators whose insiders or affiliates have
9 outstanding contempt citations or fines as of June 7, 1989, shall be
10 required to post Category B surety.
11 3. Operators using Category A surety who are assessed a fine of
12 Two Thousand Dollars ($2,000.00) or more and who do not pay the fine
13 within the specified time shall be required to post a Category B
14 surety within thirty (30) days of notification by the Commission.
15 C. For good cause shown concerning pollution or improper
16 plugging of wells by the operator posting either Category A or B
17 surety or by an insider or affiliate of such operator, the
18 Commission, upon application of the Director of the Oil and Gas
19 Conservation Division, after notice and hearing, may require the
20 filing of additional Category B surety in an amount greater than
21 Twenty-five Thousand Dollars ($25,000.00) but not to exceed One
22 Hundred Fifty Thousand Dollars ($150,000.00).
23 D. If the Commission determines that a blanket surety bond is
24 required, the bond shall be conditioned on the fact that the
SB1976 HFLR Page 6
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 oper ator shall cause the wells to be plugged and abandoned surface
2 impoundments to be closed, and trash and equipment to be removed in
3 accordance with the laws of this state and the rules of the
4 Commission. Each bond shall be executed by a corporate surety
5 authorized to do business in this state and shall be renewed and
6 continued in effect until the conditions have been met or release of
7 the bond is authorized by the Commission.
8 E. The agreement provided for in subsection A of this section
9 shall provide that if the Commission determines that the person
10 furnishing the agreement has neglected, failed, or refused to plug
11 and abandon, or cause to be plugged and abandoned, or replug any
12 well or has neglected, failed, or refused to close any surface
13 impoundment or removed or cause to be removed trash and equipment in
14 compliance with the rules of the Commission, then the person shall
15 forfeit from his or her bond, letter of credit, or negotiable
16 instrument or shall pay to this state, through the Commission, for
17 deposit in the State Treasury, a sum equal to the cost of plugging
18 the well, closure of any surface impoundment or removal of trash and
19 equipment. The Commission may cause the remedial work to be done,
20 issuing a warrant in payment of the cost thereof drawn against the
21 monies accruing in the State Treasury from the forfeiture or
22 payment. Any monies accruing in the State Treasury by reason of a
23 determination that there has been a noncompliance with the
24 provisions of the agreement or the rules of the Commission, in
SB1976 HFLR Page 7
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 exce ss of the cost of remedial action ordered by the Commission,
2 shall be credited to the Oil and Gas Division Revolving Fund. The
3 Commission shall also recover any costs arising from litigation to
4 enforce this provision. Provided, before a person is required to
5 forfeit or pay any monies to the state pursuant to this section, the
6 Commission shall notify the person at his or her last-known last
7 known address of the determination of neglect, failure, or refusal
8 to plug or replug any well, or close any surface impoundment or
9 remove trash and equipment and said the person shall have ten (10)
10 days from the date of notification within which to commence remedial
11 operations. Failure to commence remedial operations shall result in
12 forfeiture or payment as provided in this subsection.
13 F. It shall be unlawful for any person to drill or operate any
14 oil or gas well subject to the provisions of this section, without
15 the evidence of financial ability required by this section. The
16 Commission shall shut in, without notice, hearing, or order of the
17 Commission, the wells of any such person violating the provisions of
18 this subsection and such wells shall remain shut in for
19 noncompliance until the required evidence of Category B surety is
20 obtained and verified by the Commission.
21 G. If title to property or a well is transferred, the
22 transferee shall furnish the evidence of financial ability to plug
23 the well and close surface impoundments required by the provisions
24 of this section, prior to the transfer.
SB1976 HFLR Page 8
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 H. As used in this section:
2 1. “Affiliate” means an entity that owns twenty percent (20%)
3 or more of the operator, or an entity of which twenty percent (20%)
4 or more is owned by the operator; and
5 2. “Insider” means officer, director, or person in control of
6 the operator; general partners of or in the operator; general or
7 limited partnership in which the operator is a general partner;
8 spouse of an officer, director, or person in control of the
9 operator; spouse of a general partner of or in the operator;
10 corporation of which the operator is a director, officer, or person
11 in control; affiliate, or insider of an affiliate as if such
12 affiliate were the operator; or managing agent of the operator.
13 SECTION 2. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
14 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
15 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
16 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
